.H 1 "Overview of DCE Maintenance"
.P
Once you have performed the tasks required for planning, installing, and
configuring your DCE system, you can go on to perform the tasks required
for maintaining the system.
The initial tasks of planning, installing, and configuring are performed
infrequently, some only once.
Maintenance tasks, however, are performed on a regular basis throughout
the lifetime of your system.
.P
Maintenance of a distributed system includes the following areas:
.ML
.LI
Performance tuning
.LI
Configuration control
.LI
Security and access control
.LE
.P
This chapter summarizes some of the primary
DCE administration tasks.
The first section of this chapter tells you how to start up DCE.  The remaining
sections describe tasks that apply to the individual components of DCE. 
DCE component tasks are documented in detail in
...\" Parts 2 through 8 of this guide.
the \*(Ac, \*(Ad, and \*(Ax.
.H 2 "Starting Up DCE"
The \*Ldce_config\*O script, which is described in 
...\" previous 
Chapters 6, 7, and 8,
creates an \*L/etc/rc.dce\*O file to start up the DCE processes.
This file is customized to an individual machine's configuration.
To start up the DCE processes, enter the
following command:
.iS
sh /etc/rc.dce
.iE
.cS
.H 3 "Replicating the Cell Namespace"
.iX "cell namespace" "replicating"
Directory replication is the most reliable way to back up the information in
your namespace.  Use the DCE control program (\*Ldcecp\*O) to create replicas
of namespace directories at a CDS clearinghouse.  Clearinghouses need to be
created in the root directory (\*L/.:\*O) of the cell namespace.
.P
The cell namespace is replicated by directory.  This means that when you
replicate a directory, all of the entries in it are automatically replicated.
The root directory is automatically replicated when you create a clearinghouse.
.P
It is recommended that you have at least two copies of each cell namespace
directory to ensure the entire namespace is available at all times.
Follow
these guidelines for replicating parts of the cell namespace:
.ML
.LI
.LI
Replicate the \*Lhosts\*O directory and below.
.LI
Replicate \*Lsubsys\*O and below.
.LE
